cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the development of automatic tools for assessing motor function in Parkinson's disease patients using mouse tracking data collected during people's interaction with a search engine. Therefore, the most likely category is Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), followed by Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves feature extraction and classification, which could fall under Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), respectively.
